headlines.description: — Darius Garland hit eight 3-pointers and scored 29 points, Evan Mobley had 22 points and 17 rebounds and the short-handed Cleveland Cavaliers held off the Detroit Pistons 110-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mobley, Garland lead short-handed Cavaliers past Pistons, 110-100

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid might still be the 76ers' MVP this season for his role as team counselor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tobias Harris breaks out of slump with 31 points, 12 rebounds, leads 76ers past Hornets 121-114

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum made five 3-pointers and scored 32 points and the Boston Celtics overcame Luka Doncic's second straight triple-double to beat the Dallas Mavericks 138-110 on Friday night and extend their season-best winning streak to 10 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics overcome Doncic's triple-double to beat Mavericks 138-110 for 10th straight win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 25 points, Jonathan Kuminga had 24 and the Golden State Warriors overcame a short night of rest and extended their road winning streak to eight games by beating the Toronto Raptors 120-105 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry leads Warriors past Raptors for 8th straight road win. Toronto star Barnes breaks finger

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Dalano Banton scored a season-high 19 points, Jabari Walker also had 19 points and 10 rebounds and the Portland Trail Blazers snapped a nine-game skid by defeating the Memphis Grizzlies 122-92 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers end 9-game skid by beating Grizzlies 122-92

headlines.description: — Malik Monk scored 35 of his 39 points after halftime and the Sacramento Kings defeated the Minnesota Timberwolves 124-120 in overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Malik Monk scores 39 to lead Kings past Timberwolves in overtime

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 19 of his 34 points in New Orleans’ franchise record-tying 48-point first quarter and the Pelicans beat the Indiana Pacers 129-102 on Friday night to split a home-and-home set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans tie franchise record with 48-point 1st quarter, rout Pacers 129-102

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks are tuning up for what they hope will be a deep playoff run. They're hitting more of the right notes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo has 46 points, 16 rebounds in Bucks' 113-97 victory over Bulls
